This man allegedly told his executioners “I hope that all of you will follow me” as he was killed in
Ramla. This man, who briefly lived at 14 Garibaldi Street in Buenos Aires, was attacked while bringing
flowers to his wife on their silver wedding anniversary. This man lived under the alias of Ricardo Klement
when he was caught by Simon Wiesenthal. Hannah Arendt coined the phrase “banality of evil” to describe
this man during his trial in Israel, after which he was executed in 1962. For the point, name this Nazi who
organized much of the Holocaust.=====
Adolf Eichmann
